I count each one of them,
because that thing still lurks somewhere.
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-agatha">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Agatha</span>
That thing is far away!
It never left the village, don't you remember?
You can't keep me here forever!
Since that flesh monstrosity attacked,
since we got to this neighborhood,
I've never been out!
For 1853 days,
tomorrow 1854.
For how long do you intend to keep this?
I want to live!
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Dad</span>
Agatha, hear at what you're saying!
You're [d]elusional—
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-agatha">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Agatha</span>
No, YOU are delusional!
I've been trapped in a basement for FIVE years.
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Dad</span>
FIVE years in which nothing has happened to you.
You're safe here!
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-agatha">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Agatha</span>
I'm trapped!
</div>
</div>
<span class="bms-convo-ellipsis">…</span>
<div class="bms-convo-poem align-left">That's it, here what I'm going to do:
You'll open that door.
I'm going for a walk.
I don't care what time it is.
I'm breathing some fresh air.</div>
<div class="bms-convo-block">
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Dad</span>
Sweetie, you can't do that.
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-agatha">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Agatha</span>
Who are you to impede such a thing?
</div>
</div>
<div class="bms-convo-poem align-left">Metal teased my poor cranium,
a supposedly small bite.
It left mark, the piercing of its teeth,
the blossom of the coagulation.
Into sleep, the venomous fangs.</div>
<span class="bms-convo-ellipsis">…</span>
<div class="bms-convo-block">
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Dad</span>
Is there anything you want for your birthday?
</div>
</div>
<div class="bms-convo-poem align-left">Suddenly, fallen down, slipped.
A small gift from the heaven,
an obsequious flyer!
I began reading.
It was excavated by my needs.</div>
<div class="bms-convo-block">
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-agatha">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Agatha</span>
This is what I want, dad.
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Dad</span>
Are you sure, sweetie?
No more gifts until next year—
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-agatha">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Agatha</span>
Just buy it and give it to me.
</div>
<div class="bms-convo-poem align-left">
Just bought and given to you!
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-narrative mw-customtoggle-s1d">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-narrative">
<span class="bms-section-label">tO neural deficienCy?</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s1d">
<div class="bms-narrative-inner">
<div class="bms-poem-block align-left">
Since then, the butterfly eggs carved
deep below my pores.
Every string of hair wa[s] made to
smoothen the laid-down eggs.
Cutaneous, I dare to think.
Arrived!
Just a drop, they say.
I'll try my new gift!
So the maelstrom was unle[a]shed from the different wrinkles.
</div>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-drug mw-customtoggle-s2d">
<div class="bms-drug-bg"></div>
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-drug">
<span class="bms-section-label">To fake colors?</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s2d">
<div class="bms-drug-inner">
<div class="bms-drug-poem align-left">
<span class="bms-rainbow">the wine began cascading!</span>
<span class="bms-melt">stroboscopic glass</span>
carbonated methanol
<span class="bms-shake">dancing with myself</span>
amalgamated with arms and legs
the longing of the arachnid legs
<span class="bms-dissolve">butterflies now wingless</span>
spring arrived to my alveolar cavities
a trip inside corridors of calcium deposits
it was when i came back
polydactyl caverns
<span class="bms-glitch">never stop filling the bottle</span>
shards in his mouth, eyes, ears
the frog hadn't developed legs
soliloquy of his
the house of green was a capsule
in state of decay, hearts of a garden
<span class="bms-rainbow">her eyes of violet were gorgeous</span>
indiscernible from the above blue
with its arachnid legs, there, horizon
joints hid the thorax
a task never dared to be done
forever refused to vanish monthly red
<span class="bms-melt">she preferred to be consumed by maggots</span>
and then black
and then white.
</div>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-narrative mw-customtoggle-s1e">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-narrative">
<span class="bms-section-label">Was life made to be so bitter</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s1e">
<div class="bms-narrative-inner">
<div class="bms-poem-block align-left">
It's unbearable to see my
skin necrose because of the drink.
Only thing that allows me to exit.
Only thing I care about.
He'd look me with this adipose face.
Over itself, a wavy beard intertwined.
Deeply black, hematomas were too.
Fistulas are just the new rot!
The drink sat there, the butterfly eggs.
They were about to be born serenely.
Innocently anchoring to my deep breath
and rushed towards exhalation.
But suddenly, green sprung.
Sprang acid all over the floor,
the undigested eggs back to genesis.
My sweet protective angel rushed.
The floor, what a mess!
He ignored the [v]aporizing substance and
sprinted towards me.
His ever-loving smile faded,
aside from the slightest hate.
He kept whispering to himself,
"I'm sorry, I'm sorry!"
the door slightly opened.
And the light was to hit me right in the face.
</div>
<span class="bms-ellipsis">…</span>
<div class="bms-poem-block align-left">
A real light, the sun.
The sun!
He looked pitiful at my trashed state,
at my disposable body.
</div>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-convo mw-customtoggle-s4b">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-convo">
<span class="bms-section-label">……</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s4b">
<div align="center";>
<br>
Just this onc[e].<br>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-narrative mw-customtoggle-s1f">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-narrative">
<span class="bms-section-label">I am its victim</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s1f">
<div class="bms-narrative-inner">
<div class="bms-poem-block align-left">
Merrily, my lachrymals into work.
It built up a tension,
my sinews so uptight they would almost tear.
The fresh air of the outside was almost there…!
The steps the only obstacle.
</div>
<div class="bms-poem-block align-center">
Step.
Step.
Step.
</div>
<div class="bms-poem-block align-center">
…?
</div>
<div class="bms-poem-block align-left">
My leg wouldn't budge.
It wouldn't move.
Be functional, please!
It negated horribly, sticking to ground.
Almost.
Almost!
It was STUPID to think that would work.
It was HORRIBLE to even consider escape a option.
Yet it wasn't he, it was ME.
If I had only waited a bit…
Father looked:
</div>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-convo mw-customtoggle-s4c">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-convo">
<span class="bms-section-label">its scapegoat</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s4c">
<div class="bms-convo-inner">
<div class="bms-convo-block">
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Dad</span>
Don't you want to escape?
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div class="bms-section bms-narrative mw-customtoggle-s1g">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-narrative">
<span class="bms-section-label">……</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s1g">
<div class="bms-narrative-inner">
<div class="bms-poem-block align-left">
Yet it was the collar of butterflies
and the whip of wine which wouldn't
let me do so.
</div>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-convo mw-customtoggle-s4d">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-convo">
<span class="bms-section-label">Only one option</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s4d">
<div class="bms-convo-inner">
<div class="bms-convo-block">
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Dad</span>
Agatha, listen to me!
</div>
<div class="bms-poem-block align-left">
Why had that [m]onster to appear?
Why wouldn't I live now in the village?
Why did I have to survive?
</div>
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
<span class="bms-speech-label">Dad</span>
I guess you aren't in the mood…
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-narrative mw-customtoggle-s1h">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-narrative">
<span class="bms-section-label">Horridly abused</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s1h">
<div class="bms-narrative-inner">
<div class="bms-poem-block align-left">
Yet I was and I wasn't.
yet I needed to yearn and needed
to cut my hope short.
Yet pollen in the air.
</div>
</div>

<div class="bms-section bms-convo mw-customtoggle-s4e">
<div class="bms-section-header bms-section-title-convo">
<span class="bms-section-label">No return now</span>
</div>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-s4e">
<div class="bms-convo-inner">
<div class="bms-convo-block">
<div class="bms-speech-line speaker-dad">
